-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Refiner Mol Are Active in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-12T08:44:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-are-active-in-budapest.html
Hungary’s benchmark BUX stock index
rose 0.6 percent to 17,979.91 as of 10:31 a.m. in Budapest. The
following were among the most active equities in the Hungarian
market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender,
rebounded from the lowest close in almost three months as the
Federal Reserve said the U.S. economy continues to expand,
boosting bets on a recovery in the world economy. The shares
advanced 0.8 percent to 3,628 forint.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, gained 0.5
percent to 17,360 forint. Oil rose for a second day in New York
after fuel stockpiles declined more than expected.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
